  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(7) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Moreover I will establish his kingdom for ever.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—So ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Chronicles 22:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (at end).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "If he be constant to do my commandments and my judgments.—The same condition is attached to the same promise in 1Kings 9:4-5. (Comp. also 1Kings 3:14, where the promise is length of days.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "If he be constant to do my commandments and my judgments.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The same condition is attached to the same promise in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Kings 9:4-5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". (Comp. also ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Kings 3:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", where the promise is length of days.)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As at this day.—As we are doing in our present work. The same words occur in the same sense at the end of Solomon’s Prayer (1Kings 8:61).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "As at this day.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
